This paper is about a novel generative model that combines supervised and unsupervised learning to obtain interpretable global representations for each class of data. The model is evaluated on a machine learning benchmark dataset (MNIST) and gene expression data (LINCS), indicating that it has applications in various fields such as computer vision, natural language processing, and neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
